headline: 3 Reasons MNST Has Explosive Upside Potential
summary: Monster’s 29.6% return over the past six months has outpaced the S&P 500 by 18.5%, and its stock price has climbed to $77.31 per share. This was partly due to its solid quarterly results, and the run-up might have investors contemplating their next move.
